title: Heavy rain batters parts of Spain as residents urged to stay indoors
description: Railway lines have been closed, a football match has been cancelled and residents have been ordered to stay indoors after heavy rain in parts of Spain.

title: US jail in lockdown with around 100 prisoners 'refusing to return to cells'
description: A US jail has been placed under an emergency lockdown after about 100 prisoners refused to return to their cells.

title: Boy thrown from 10th floor of Tate Modern now mostly out of wheelchair
description: A boy thrown from the 10th floor of the Tate Modern art gallery is now mostly out of his wheelchair, his family says.

title: Benjamin Netanyahu plans to deport all African migrants from Israel after Eritrean groups involved in violent clashes
description: Plans should be drawn up to remove all African migrants from Israel after groups of Eritreans were involved in a violent clash in Tel Aviv,  Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu says.

title: Man set to get over £110,000 in compensation after great-grandfather hanged by Nazis
description: Relatives of six Italian men hanged by German troops during World War Two are set to receive hundreds of thousands of euros in compensation for their families' trauma.

title: Mason Greenwood's new manager says loan signing is 'delicate issue'
description: Mason Greenwood's new manager has said signing the player is a "delicate issue" that is "kind of a tough situation to talk about".
